Self-care is important, but self-care for kids looks like bathing and drinking enough water. What is this supposed to do for a kid that their body can't already do (or a doctor-prescribed routine if they have a medical condition)? Adults do things for their skin because skin changes as it ages, and it makes no sense to do for young skin what it can do for itself. I say this as someone who found out that almost everything wrong with my skin simply came from not drinking enough water.
